        <updateDate>2021-11-20T20:10:58Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Drug Price Transparency Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill provides statutory authority for the limitation on which type of prescription drug rebates are exempt from federal anti-kickback laws.<br> <br> Specifically, a rebate from a drug manufacturer to a health insurer or pharmacy benefit manager is exempt only if the rebate (1) is disclosed to the consumer at the point of sale, or (2) is a flat fee paid for pharmacy benefit management services.<br> </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
